<!--
Task definition rules:
- Each task MUST have Requirements (linked FR), Depends (dependency), Files (targets)
- Verify must be a concrete command: "task test passes" "curl localhost:7575/api/X returns 200" etc.
- S: ~30min, 1 file | M: ~1-2h, multi-file | L: ~2-4h, complex logic
- (P) suffix marks parallel-safe tasks

Task decomposition principles:
- 1 task = 1 responsibility. "Create A, wire B, test C" = 3 separate tasks
- Max 3-4 changed files per task. Split if more
- DB schema changes and logic using them = separate tasks (migration first)
- Tests go WITH the implementation task (not separate). Verify confirms tests pass
- If frontend and backend are independent, make them parallel tasks (P)

Bad examples:
  T-1.1 [L] Build API + DB + frontend all at once → too large, unreviewable
  T-1.1 [S] Write code / T-1.2 [S] Write tests → tests belong with implementation

Good examples:
  T-1.1 [M] DB schema + migration + tests
  T-1.2 [M] API endpoint + tests (Depends: T-1.1)
  T-1.3 [M] (P) Frontend UI (Depends: T-1.2 types only)
-->

